HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 118
BY REPRESENTATIVES WRIGHT AND JACKSON
A RESOLUTION
To create and provide with respect to a select committee of the House of Representatives to
study the potential establishment of a state income tax credit for water utility
customers who pay excessive rates for residential water service and to report findings
and recommendations to the members of the House of Representatives no later than
thirty days prior to the convening of the 2027 Regular Session.
WHEREAS, the Legislature of Louisiana places a high priority on ensuring the
availability of safe and affordable drinking water for the citizens of this state; and
WHEREAS, the Louisiana Public Service Commission (PSC) regulates privately
owned water utilities in this state through oversight of those utilities' service quality,
regulatory compliance, and rates; and
WHEREAS, despite PSC oversight of water utility rates, many utility customers pay
excessive charges for their residential water service; and
WHEREAS, the legislature frequently considers bills proposing tax preferences for
individuals facing various forms of financial hardship; and
WHEREAS, it is appropriate to call for a study to determine whether a viable
solution involving tax policy exists for the problem of excessive rates charged to residential
water utility customers.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby create a select committee to study the potential
establishment of a state income tax credit for water utility customers who pay excessive rates
for residential water service.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the select committee shall be named the "Select
House Committee on Water Utility Tax Credits" and shall be composed of the following
seven members:
